# Content Management Guidelines

## Content Collections
Content for Grobles' portfolio (blog posts, case studies, project showcases) is managed through Astro's content collections system defined in [content.config.ts](mdc:src/content.config.ts).

## Content Schema
All content (blog posts, case studies, project showcases) must include:
- `title: string` - Post title
- `description: string` - Post description
- `pubDate: Date` - Publication date (auto-coerced from string)
- `updatedDate?: Date` - Optional update date
- `heroImage?: ImageMetadata` - Optional hero image

## Content Location
- Blog posts, case studies, project showcases: `src/content/blog/`
- Supported formats: `.md` and `.mdx`
- Assets: `src/assets/` for images, project screenshots, etc.

## File Naming
- Use kebab-case for blog post filenames
- Example: `my-awesome-post.md`

## Frontmatter Example
```yaml
---
title: "My Blog Post"
description: "A description of my post"
pubDate: "2024-01-15"
updatedDate: "2024-01-20"
heroImage: "../../assets/my-image.jpg"
---
```

## Global Constants
Site-wide constants are defined in [consts.ts](mdc:src/consts.ts):
- `SITE_TITLE` - Site title
- `SITE_DESCRIPTION` - Site description

Update these constants when changing site metadata.